              "content": "# mermaid\nCreate professional Mermaid diagrams using the OneGS dark palette (sapphire + teal)\n\n# Mermaid Diagrams\n\n`GS_MERMAID_THEME` is pre-imported. ALWAYS prepend it to any Mermaid string.\n\n## Basic Usage\n```python\ndiagram = GS_MERMAID_THEME + \"\"\"\ngraph TD\n    A[Start] --> B[Process]\n    B --> C[End]\n\"\"\"\nsave_artifact(diagram, \"My Diagram\", artifact_type=\"diagram\")\n```\n\n## Diagram Types\n`graph TD` \u2014 top-down flowcharts, hierarchies | `graph LR` \u2014 left-right pipelines |\n`sequenceDiagram` \u2014 API interactions | `classDiagram` \u2014 data models | `erDiagram` \u2014 ER diagrams\n\n## Node Shapes\n`A[Label]` rectangle | `A(Label)` rounded | `A{Label}` diamond | `A[(Label)]` database | `A((Label))` circle\n\n## Examples\n\n### System Architecture\n```python\ndiagram = GS_MERMAID_THEME + \"\"\"\ngraph TD\n    User([User]) -->|Uploads| API[FastAPI]\n    API --> DB[(DuckDB)]\n    DB --> Agent{AI Agent}\n    Agent -->|Artifacts| UI[Dashboard]\n    style User fill:#1a2038,stroke:#3d7be8,stroke-width:2px,color:#e8ecf4\n    style Agent fill:#1a2038,stroke:#2eb89a,stroke-width:2px,color:#e8ecf4\n    style DB fill:#12172b,stroke:#e8a820,stroke-width:2px,color:#e8ecf4\n\"\"\"\nsave_artifact(diagram, \"System Architecture\", artifact_type=\"diagram\")\n```\n\n### Sequence Diagram\n```python\ndiagram = GS_MERMAID_THEME + \"\"\"\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant U as User\n    participant A as Agent\n    participant D as DuckDB\n    U->>A: Ask question\n    A->>D: SQL query\n    D-->>A: Result set\n    A-->>U: Answer + chart\n\"\"\"\nsave_artifact(diagram, \"Request Flow\", artifact_type=\"diagram\")\n```\n\n## Rules\n1. ALWAYS prepend `GS_MERMAID_THEME`\n2. Use `artifact_type=\"diagram\"` in `save_artifact()`\n3. Highlight 1-3 key nodes with `style` overrides: `fill:#1a2038,stroke:#3d7be8,stroke-width:2px,color:#e8ecf4`\n4. Prefer `LR` for pipelines, `TD` for hierarchies\n5. Max ~15 nodes before splitting into subgraphs. Labels \u22645 words.\n\n---\n**YOU ARE NOT DONE.** The user asked for a CHART, not a table. You MUST call `run_python` NOW with a script that queries the data AND draws the chart. Follow the template above exactly. Pre-imported: `gs_theme`, `save_artifact`, `PRIMARY`, `CAT_PALETTE`, `_db`. Use `:Q` for numbers, `:N` for categories, `:T` for dates only.",
